{{Quote|We're a family. Family does for family.|[[Soontir Fel/Legends|Soontir Fel]]|<ref name="Rogue Squadron 25" />}}
The '''Fel dynasty''' was a prominent [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] family that was known for its [[Imperial Military/Legends|military service]] to the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] and the [[Empire of the Hand]] before ascending to become the ruling house of the [[Imperial Remnant]] and re-organizing it as the [[Fel Empire]]. Before the ascension of [[Jagged Fel]], the first of the Fel [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperors]], his family&mdash;or at least, his parents&mdash;were media stars of the first [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] and later associated with the [[Empire of the Hand]] and the [[Chiss Ascendancy/Legends|Chiss Ascendancy]]. At least three members were dedicated soldiers&mdash;[[Soontir Fel/Legends|Soontir Fel]] was one of the Empire's most decorated pilots and his son Jagged flew with distinction during the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]]. The family was also linked to one of the most famous [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebellion]] and later on [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] families, the [[Antilles family/Legends|Antilles family]] of [[Corellia/Legends|Corellia]], by marriage through [[Syal Antilles Fel]], though due to their different positions in the political fabric of [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]], they had little contact for much of the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].

Following the conclusion of the [[Second Galactic Civil War]], the Fel family's ties to the [[Galactic Federation of Free Alliances|Galactic Alliance]] were reinforced with the marriage of Jagged Fel to [[Jaina Solo Fel|Jaina]] of the [[Solo family/Legends|House of Solo]]. Jagged's descendants ruled the Fel Empire until [[Darth Krayt]]'s coup of [[130 ABY]], which overthrew Emperor [[Roan Fel]], the third Fel Emperor. Following a [[Second Imperial Civil War|period of civil war]] between [[Empire-in-exile|Fel's faction]] and [[Darth Krayt's Galactic Empire|Krayt's faction]], the Fel dynasty was restored under Roan's daughter [[Marasiah Fel|Marasiah]] as the Empire's first [[Empress/Legends|Empress]].

==Members==
===1st Generation===
*[[Soontir Fel's father|Unidentified male]], a transport flier on [[Corellia/Legends|Corellia]], Soontir Fel's father.
*[[Soontir Fel's mother|Unidentified female]], his wife, Soontir Fel's mother.

===2nd Generation===
*[[Soontir Fel/Legends|Soontir Fel]], [[Baron of the Empire/Legends|Imperial baron]] and fighter pilot.
*[[Syal Antilles Fel]] (also known as Wynssa Starflare), Soontir's wife, famous actress.
*[[Todr Fel]], Soontir's younger brother.
*[[Ajai Fel]], Todr's wife and Soontir's sister-in-law.

===3rd Generation===
*[[Davin Fel]], Soontir's eldest son, [[Empire of the Hand]] officer.
*[[Chak Fel]], Soontir's son, Empire of the Hand officer.
*[[Jagged Fel]], Soontir's son, first [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] of the [[Fel Empire]] and founder of the Fel dynasty.
*[[Jaina Solo Fel]], Jagged's wife, [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] of the [[New Jedi Order]]
*[[Cherith Fel]], Soontir and Syal's eldest daughter.
*[[Cem Fel]], Soontir and Syal's youngest son and [[shadow child]].
*[[Wynssa Fel]], Soontir and Syal's youngest daughter.
*[[Fyric Fel]], Todr and Ajai Fel's son.

===4th Generation===
*[[Fel II]], Jagged Fel's son, second Fel Emperor.

===5th Generation===
*[[Roan Fel]], son of Fel II and third member of the Fel family in succession to reign as Emperor.
*[[Elliah Fel]], Roan's wife and mother of Marasiah, killed by [[Darth Havok|Eshkar Niin]].
*[[Mohrgan Fel]], Roan's cousin and [[Imperial Knight]].

===6th Generation===
*[[Marasiah Fel]], Roan and Elliah's daughter, first Empress of the [[Fel Empire]] and Triumvir of the [[Galactic Federation Triumvirate]].

===Others===
Soontir Fel was also used as a template for [[Cloning/Legends|clones]] during [[Grand Admiral/Legends|Grand Admiral]] [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo/Legends|Thrawn's]] [[Thrawn campaign|campaign]]. These clones were used as sleeper cells, and scattered throughout the New Republic. One such cell, led by Soontir Fel's clone [[Carib Devist]], defected to the New Republic.

